'''''UFC 194: Aldo vs. McGregor''''' was a [[mixed martial arts]]  event held by the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]] on December 12, 2015, at the [[MGM Grand Garden Arena]] in [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]], Nevada.<ref name="UFC194">{{cite news|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/blogs/mma-cagewriter/dana-white--aldo-mcgregor-set-for-dec--12-at-mgm-grand-in-las-vegas-004231499.html|title=Dana White: Aldo-McGregor set for Dec. 12 at MGM Grand in Las Vegas|publisher=sports.yahoo.com|author=Kevin Iole|date=2015-08-10|access-date=2015-08-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://ufc.com/news/Aldo-vs-McGregor-Finds-a-Home-in-Vegas-on-Dec-12|title=Aldo vs. McGregor finds a home in Vegas on Dec. 12|publisher=ufc.com|author=Thomas Gerbasi|date=2015-08-11|access-date=2015-08-11}}</ref>

==Background==
The event was originally scheduled to take place on December 5. However, the [[MGM Grand Garden Arena]] had already been booked for an [[Andrea Bocelli]] concert, prompting the UFC to look at alternative venues such as the [[Mandalay Bay Events Center]]. The [[AT&T Stadium]] in [[Arlington, Texas]] was the most relevant venue under consideration, which would likely have made the event the highest attended in the promotion's history.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dallasnews.com/sports/more-sports/headlines/20150716-report-att-stadium-being-looked-at-for-ufc-194-which-could-feature-fight-between-jose-aldo-conor-mcgregor.ece|title=Report: AT&T Stadium being looked at for UFC 194, which could feature fight between Jose Aldo, Conor McGregor and Prady who is Mcgregors best friend.|publisher=dallasnews.com|author=Staff|date=2015-07-16|access-date=2015-08-11}}</ref> Subsequently, on August 10, UFC president [[Dana White]] confirmed the event would take place at the MGM Grand Garden Arena, albeit one week later on December 12.<ref name="UFC194"/>
[[File:José Aldo vs. Conor McGregor, UFC 189 World Tour London.jpg|300px|thumb|left|McGregor (right), Dana White (middle) and [[José Aldo]] (left) prior to the [[UFC 189]] press conference in March 2015.]]
This event marked the first time the UFC has ever scheduled three events in consecutive days, with all of them taking place in Las Vegas. Instead of the MGM Grand Garden Arena, the other two events were held at [[Cosmopolitan of Las Vegas|The Chelsea at The Cosmopolitan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmafighting.com/2015/9/4/9263143/ufc-to-run-three-las-vegas-events-in-span-of-three-days-in-december|title=UFC to run three Las Vegas events in span of three days in December|publisher=mmafighting.com|author=Marc Raimondi|date=2015-09-04|access-date=2015-09-04}}</ref>

The event was headlined by a [[UFC Featherweight Championship]] unification bout between then champion [[José Aldo]] and then interim champion [[Conor McGregor]].<ref name="UFC194"/> The bout was originally expected to take place at [[UFC 189]]. However, Aldo pulled out of the bout due to a rib injury and the event was instead headlined by an interim title bout between McGregor and [[Chad Mendes]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2015/06/jose-aldo-officially-out-of-ufc-189-chad-mendes-meets-conor-mcgregor-for-interim-belt|title=Jose Aldo officially out of UFC 189; Chad Mendes meets Conor McGregor for interim belt|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Matt Erickson|date=2015-06-30|access-date=2015-08-10}}</ref>

The co-main event featured a [[UFC Middleweight Championship]] bout between then undefeated champion [[Chris Weidman]] and former [[List of Strikeforce champions#Middleweight Championship|Strikeforce Middleweight champion]] [[Luke Rockhold]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ufc.com/news/Weidman-vs-Rockhold-is-UFC-194-Co-Main-Event|title=Weidman vs. Rockhold is UFC 194 co-main event|publisher=ufc.com|author=Thomas Gerbasi|date=2015-08-13|access-date=2015-08-13}}</ref>

A middleweight bout between [[Ronaldo Souza]] and [[Yoel Romero]] was originally booked for [[UFC 184]] and later ''[[UFC on Fox: Machida vs. Rockhold]]''. However, the bout was cancelled both times due to Souza being struck with pneumonia<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmafighting.com/2015/1/15/7555065/ufc-184-fight-card-jacare-souza-out-pneumonia-vs-yoel-romero-scratched|title='Jacare' Souza out with pneumonia, bout against Yoel Romero scratched from UFC 184|publisher=mmafighting.com|author=Shaun Al-Shatti|date=2015-01-15|access-date=2015-08-17}}</ref> and Romero pulling out due to a ligament and meniscus tear in his knee, respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmafighting.com/2015/4/10/8384799/yoel-romero-injured-out-of-ufc-on-fox-15-bout-opposite-jacare-souza|title=Yoel Romero injured, out of UFC on FOX 15 bout opposite Jacare Souza|publisher=mmafighting.com|author=Luke Thomas|date=2015-04-10|access-date=2015-08-17}}</ref> The fight was later rescheduled for this event.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2015/08/yoel-romero-vs-ronaldo-jacare-souza-booked-for-ufc-194-in-december|title=Yoel Romero vs. Ronaldo 'Jacare' Souza booked for UFC 194 in December|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Staff|date=2015-08-17|access-date=2015-08-17}}</ref>

[[Michelle Waterson]] was expected to face [[Tecia Torres]] at the event. However, Waterson pulled out of the bout on November 24 citing an injury.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2015/11/super-card-takes-a-hit-michelle-waterson-out-of-ufc-194-replacement-sought|title=Super card takes a hit: Michelle Waterson out of UFC 194|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Dann Stupp and John Morgan|date=2015-11-24|access-date=2015-11-24}}</ref> She was replaced by
promotional newcomer [[Jocelyn Jones-Lybarger]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mmajunkie.com/2015/11/rfa-champ-jocelyn-jones-lybarger-steps-in-against-tecia-torres-at-ufc-194|title=RFA champ Jocelyn Jones-Lybarger steps in against Tecia Torres at UFC 194|publisher=mmajunkie.com|author=Staff|date=2015-11-27|access-date=2015-11-27}}</ref>

On January 13, Romero was informed of a potential doping violation stemming from an out of competition test conducted by [[USADA]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ufc.com/news/UFC-Statement-on-Yoel-Romero-11216?nd=1|title=UFC statement on Yoel Romero|publisher=ufc.com|author=Staff|date=2016-01-13|access-date=2016-01-13}}</ref> On February 8, Romero and his manager explained that he took a supplement after his fight and that supplement turned out to be contaminated. His team and USADA both sent out the supplement for testing and it came back that it contained a banned substance. That substance was not listed on the label, his manager said. They did not want to reveal the name of the supplement or the substance, because USADA was investigating the issue.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmafighting.com/2016/2/8/10941272/manager-contaminated-supplement-led-to-yoel-romeros-failed-drug-test|title=Manager: Contaminated supplement led to Yoel Romero's failed drug test|publisher=mmafighting.com|author=Marc Raimondi|date=2016-02-08|access-date=2016-02-09}}</ref> On March 23, it was announced that Romero would appeal his suspension. His team and USADA discussed a deal for a nine-month suspension for the fighter, but Romero preferred to go to arbitration. The typical USADA anti-doping violation suspension is two years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmafighting.com/2016/3/23/11295456/yoel-romero-to-appeal-usada-suspension-for-anti-doping-policy|title=Yoel Romero to appeal USADA suspension for anti-doping policy violation|publisher=mmafighting.com|author=Marc Raimondi|date=2016-03-23|access-date=2016-03-23}}</ref> Eventually on April 4, both parts reached an agreement for a six-month suspension. USADA revealed that Romero tested positive for [[ibutamoren]], a [[growth hormone]] release stimulator. The supplement was tested and the banned substance did indeed come up, even though it was not listed on the label. Romero announced that he'll pursue legal action against the supplement company within the next few weeks. The result of the fight was not disqualified or overturned.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmafighting.com/2016/4/4/11364368/yoel-romero-gets-six-month-suspension-from-usada-for-failing-drug|title=Yoel Romero gets six-month suspension from USADA for failing drug test due to contaminated supplement|publisher=mmafighting.com|author=Marc Raimondi|date=2016-04-04|access-date=2016-04-04}}</ref>

==McGregor vs. Aldo fight==
Before the opening of the first round, they refused to touch gloves and went immediately into combat.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mmafighting.com/2015/12/13/9994502/ufc-194-live-blog-jose-aldo-vs-conor-mcgregor|title=UFC 194 live blog: Jose Aldo vs. Conor McGregor|publisher=mmafighting.com|author=Luke Thomas|date=2015-12-13|access-date=2015-12-13}}</ref> As the fight started, McGregor took control of the center of the octagon. When Aldo got within his range, McGregor threw a straight left hand to keep Aldo away. The punch did not hit its target. McGregor then followed with a leg kick that connected. As Aldo charged forward to connect with a right-left punch combination, McGregor moved backwards and connected with a left hook that landed on Aldo's chin and rendered him unconscious. Both punches connected, but McGregor's left punch landed first. As Aldo fell to the ground, McGregor connected with two [[Strike (attack)#Hammerfist|hammer fist]]s until the referee ([[John McCarthy (referee)|Big John McCarthy]]) stepped in to stop the fight. When the fight was over, McGregor leaped atop the fence and celebrated his victory. Within a minute, Aldo regained consciousness and was on his feet.<ref name=mcgregoraldo1/> The bout lasted 13 seconds. The knockout was the fastest finish in UFC title fight history.<ref name=mcgregoraldo1/> “Again, nobody can take that left-hand shot,” said McGregor in the post-fight interview. “[Aldo's] powerful and he's fast. But precision beats power, and timing beats speed. And that’s what you saw there.”<ref name=mcgregoraldo1>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/sports/conor-mcgregor-caps-ufc-194-by-knocking-out-jose-aldo-in-13-seconds/2015/12/13/ce7eba42-a155-11e5-8728-1af6af208198_story.html|title=Conor McGregor caps UFC 194 by knocking out Jose Aldo in 13 seconds|work=washingtonpost.com|author=Jeff Wagenheim|date=2015-12-13|access-date=2015-12-13}}</ref>

